All this was done in Eclipse on Windows, if it makes any difference
Compiling and running the code should take the input file "arion.bin" and write the result of MapReduce to MapReduceResults.txt
It immediately takes the ouptput file and runs it through the class used to create the JSON file that is used by visualizer.html to visualize the data using D3.js

MongodDB has to be running on the host system before you will be able to successfully run the program.
If I understand it correctly, it shouldn't matter where it is installed. Once it is running the program will access it from 'localhost'